hands_on_practices.solution:
1. Amplitude: 
   $$\mathcal M = \frac{e^2}{s}\bigl[\bar v(p_2)\gamma^\mu u(p_1)\bigr]\bigl[\bar u(p_3)\gamma_\mu v(p_4)\bigr].$$
2. For an initial $e^-_L e^+_R$ state, summing over final $\mu^\pm$ helicities gives the squared amplitude:
   $$|\mathcal{M}|^2_{LR} = 2e^4\bigl(1+\cos^2\theta\bigr).$$
3. Differential cross-section in the COM frame:
   $$\frac{d\sigma}{d\Omega}
     =\frac{|\mathcal{M}|^2_{LR}}{64\pi^2 s}
     =\frac{2e^4(1+\cos^2\theta)}{64\pi^2 s}
     =\frac{e^4}{32\pi^2 s}(1+\cos^2\theta).$$
4. Use $e^2=4\pi\alpha$:
   $$\frac{d\sigma}{d\Omega}
     =\frac{(4\pi\alpha)^2}{32\pi^2 s}(1+\cos^2\theta)
     =\frac{16\pi^2\alpha^2}{32\pi^2 s}(1+\cos^2\theta) = \frac{\alpha^2}{2s}(1+\cos^2\theta).$$
